-- Calfrac Well Services, Magna, Sierra Wireless: Canadian Equity Preview
-- B y   M a t t   W a l c o f f
-- 2010-09-24T13:04:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/calfrac-well-services-magna-sierra-wireless-canadian-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual  moves in  Canadian trading .  Calfrac Well Services Ltd.  (CFW CT): The oilfield-services
company had its rating raised to “outperform” from “market
perform” by  Andrew Bradford , an analyst at Raymond James
Financial Inc.  Magna International Inc.  (MG CT): Canada’s largest auto-
parts maker received an “overweight” rating in new coverage
from Morgan Stanley.  Sierra Wireless Inc.  (SW CT): The maker of wireless-
communications products announced a corporate reorganization and
a workforce reduction of 6 percent. The company said it will
take a pretax charge of about $4.5 million in the third quarter
and expects to save about $1 million a quarter.  To contact the reporters on this story;
